comments: Pritchard (BOS) jumps alongside Irving (BKN) with his arm in a vertical position to contest the driving shot attempt. Any leg to leg contact after the release is deemed incidental and is created by Irving extending his legs back.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Smart (BOS) throws an errant pass out of bounds.
During the screen, Tatum (BOS) and Griffin (BKN) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Irving (BKN) is established in Tatum's (BOS) path and extends his arm out to make clean ball contact. The Replay Center confirms the call on the court that Tatum loses control of his dribble as he spins away from Irving and the ball goes out of bounds.
At the start of the drive, Tatum (BOS) makes contact to Shamet's (BKN) body and the contact affects his SQBR.
Smart (BOS) makes clean ball contact to temporarily dislodge the ball from Irving (BKN) on the perimeter.
Tatum (BOS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.

Smart (BOS) moves into and makes contact with Griffin's (BKN) body, who jumps straight up, which affects his jump shot attempt. Any contact with Smart's face is deemed incidental as Griffin has a natural shooting motion and is a result of Smart crowding Griffin.
The ball does not touch the rim on the shot by Griffin (BKN), but Tatum (BOS) is able to catch the rebound simultaneous to the 24 shot clock expiration.
Green (BKN) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage off-ball and the contact is marginal.
Griffin (BKN) makes contact to Tatum's (BOS) body and the contact affects his SQBR.
Fournier (BOS) makes contact to Shamet's (BKN) body and the contact affects his SQBR.

Tatum (BOS) places a resting hand, which he does not extend, on Green's (BKN) hip as he releases to the perimeter. The contact is marginal and does not affect Green's ability to legally contest the step back jump shot.
Brown (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Fournier (BOS) and avoids making any contact to his arm during his contest.

Harris (BKN) and Brown (BKN) reach for the ball and any contact to Parker's (BOS) arm is deemed marginal as he is able to maintain full control of the ball. Parker inadvertently steps on his teammate Fournier's (BOS) foot, which causes him to stumble.
Harris (BKN) is established in a legal guarding position with his arm in a vertical position as he absorbs the contact created by Parker (BOS) during the play at the basket.
Harris (BKN) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs with Fournier's (BOS) arm during the rebound.
Harris (BKN) is in a legal guarding position when he contests Tatum's (BOS) shot attempt at the basket and the marginal contact is created by Tatum.
Irving (BKN) makes contact with Tatum's (BOS) arm, which affects his shot near the rim.
During the rebound, Smart (BOS) and Griffin (BKN) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal as it does not affect Griffin's ability to retrieve the ball.
Smart (BOS) commits a take foul on Griffin (BKN).
During the inbound, Smart (BOS) and Shamet (BKN) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Langford (BOS) commits a take foul on Irving (BKN).
